(b)  On July 24, 2007, Align Technology, Inc. announced that it had terminated its employment relationship with Michael J. Henry, Vice President, Information Technology and Chief Information Officer effective July 23, 2007.  Len M. Hedge, Align's Vice President, Operations, will assume day-to-day responsibility for the IT department.
(e)  On July 23, 2007, the employment agreement dated December 12, 2005 between Align and Mr. Henry was terminated.  Upon such termination, Align and Mr. Henry entered into a Separation and General Release Agreement dated July 23, 2007, pursuant to which Mr. Henry is entitled to receive one hundred twenty three thousand seven hundred and fifty dollars ($123,750) to be paid in accordance with Align's standard payroll schedule and practices, less applicable deductions and withholding, which represents six months of Mr. Henry's current base salary.  In addition, Align will continue to pay the cost of Mr. Henry's group health insurance for a period of six months.
