8.7
Escrow Arrangements.
(a) . By virtue of this Agreement and as partial security for the Indemnified Parties under , at the Effective Time, Parent shall deposit with the Escrow Agent the Base Escrow Amount, the Sales Tax Escrow Amount and the Securityholder Representative Expenses Reserve, such deposit to constitute an escrow fund to be governed by the terms set forth herein. The Base Escrow Amount ( any interest paid on such Base Escrow Amount) shall be available to compensate the Indemnified Parties for any claims by such parties for any Losses suffered or incurred by them and for which they are entitled to recovery under . The Sales Tax Escrow Amount ( any interest paid on such Sales Tax Escrow Amount) shall be exclusively available to compensate the Indemnified Parties for any claims by such parties for any Losses suffered or incurred by them and for which they are entitled to recovery under . The Securityholder Representative Expenses Reserve shall be used to pay the Securityholder Representative Expenses and Advisory Committee Expenses in accordance with . The Base Escrow Amount ( any interest paid on such Base Escrow Amount), the Sales Tax Escrow Amount ( any interest paid on such Sales Tax Escrow Amount) and the Securityholder Representative Expenses Reserve ( any interest paid on such Securityholder Representative Expenses Reserve) are collectively referred to herein as the "". The Escrow Agent may execute this Agreement following the date hereof and prior to the Closing, and such later execution, if so executed after the date hereof, shall not affect the binding nature of this Agreement as of the date hereof between the other signatories hereto.
