however
(viii) The Escrow Agent may resign at any time upon giving at least 30 days written notice to Parent and the Securityholder Representative; , , that no such resignation shall become effective until the appointment of a successor escrow agent by Parent, subject to the consent of the Securityholder Representative, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed. The successor escrow agent shall execute and deliver an instrument accepting such appointment and the rights and obligations of the Escrow Agent under this Agreement, and it shall, without further acts, be vested with all the estates, properties, rights, powers, duties and obligations of the predecessor escrow agent as if originally named as escrow agent. Upon appointment of a successor escrow agent, the Escrow Agent shall be discharged from any further duties and liability under this Agreement.
