NOTE 11:-  STOCKHOLDERS' DEFICIENCY (Cont.)
 
Common stock confers upon its holders, pari passu, the right to receive notice of, and to participate in, all general meetings of the Company, to vote in such meetings, to receive dividends if declared by the Board, and to participate in the distribution of the assets of the Company in the event of liquidation of the Company in accordance with a liquidation schedule pursuant to the Company's Amended and Restated Certificate of Incorporation ("the Certificate").
 
Common A stock confers upon its holders, pari passu, the right to receive notice of, and to participate in, all general meetings of the Company, to vote in such meetings, to receive dividends if declared by the Board, and to participate in the distribution of the assets of the Company in the event of liquidation of the Company in accordance with a liquidation schedule pursuant to the Company's Certificate (see further discussion in Note 11f).
 
 
 
 
